name: Cu2+-exporting ATPase
classes: Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
reaction: ATP + H2O + Cu2+[side 1] = ADP + phosphate + Cu2+[side 2] [RN:R00086]
comment: A P-type ATPase that undergoes covalent phosphorylation during the transport cycle. The enzyme from the termophilic bacterium Archaeoglobus fulgidus is involved in copper extrusion from the cell [1,2].

references.title: Archaeoglobus fulgidus CopB is a thermophilic Cu2+-ATPase: functional role of its histidine-rich-N-terminal metal binding domain.
Conformations of the apo-, substrate-bound and phosphate-bound ATP-binding domain of the Cu(II) ATPase CopB illustrate coupling of domain movement to the catalytic cycle.
